quency. We find that, under\nsufficiently optimistic assumptions, we can recover the main features of the\nredshift evolution of the skewness in the 21cm signal. We argue that some of\nthese features - such as a dip at the onset of reionization, followed by a rise\ntowards its later stages - may be generic, and give us a promising route to a\nstatistical detection of reionization.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Sep 2008 00:32:24 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 2 Mar 2009 14:11:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-03-02"}
